def: To move up and down on the ends of a balanced plank, or thelike, as children do for sport; to seesaw; to titter; to titter-totter. [U. S.][The bobolink] alit upon the flower, and teetered up and down. H. W.Beecher.
Capable of being surmounted or overcome; superable.-- Sur*mount"a*ble*ness, n.
Of, pertaining to, or designating, an acid extracted from cacaobutter (from the Theobroma Cacao), peanut oil (from Arachis hypog√¶a),etc., as a white waxy crystalline substance.
In fact; by the act or fact. De facto. (Law) See De facto.
A measure of capacity for liquids, containing about threegallons and a haft, wine measure. It was haft the amphora, and fourtimes the congius.
One of the movable peduncles which, in the decapod Crustacea,bear the eyes at the tip.
The act of stoning. [Obs.] Bp. Hall.
